function clean_column(col)
    return Symbol(lowercase(replace(col, r"[^\w\s-]" => "")), replace(col, r"\s+|-" => "_"))
end
```

This function uses `Symbol` to ensure that the resulting string can be used as a Julia symbol. It first lowercases the column name and removes any non-word characters using `replace` with a regular expression. Then it strips leading and trailing whitespace. Finally, it replaces spaces and hyphens with underscores using another `replace` call with a different regex pattern.
